s Standard Token (PAX). It\'s another stablecoin based on Ethereum blockchain. The project is recently received negative opinion for the backdoor in their codebase that allows PAX authorities to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://cryptovest.com/news/binance-lists-paxos-pax-stablecoin-as-critics-flag-back-door-for-law-enforcement/\">freeze accounts with funds if necessary</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://atomicwallet.io/css/images/crypto-icon/DAI.svg\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>DAI is an Ethereum based Stable Coin. It differes from other stablecoins by implementing a fully decentralized technology. It\'s price is stable price is backed by&nbsp;<abbr title=\"Every DAI is backed by ETH. The token running fully on the smart contracts technology.\">Ether, not USD</abbr>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"role\">What is StableCoins role?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>StableCoins were created to solve the top problems of cryptocurrencies, such as price volatility and interaction with the real world money and markets.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To do so, Stable Coins companies make a partnership with a&nbsp;<abbr title=\"Company that issue tokens also have the same amount of USD on their account\">the issuer</abbr>&nbsp;to ensure that the price will stay the same in any cases. That also allows to easily redeem crypto to USD with no limitations. Another benefit of stablecoins — they are customer friendly. You don\'t have to think about the rates of the crypto, there are low possibility to lose the funds because of the price changing, it\'s convenient system for cross border payments.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>StableCoins are often used on major exchanges to transfer Bitcoin into USD.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"store\">Where to